{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8ad659dd-3555-4b47-bed1-f5f8c87021fd","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n**1. Remove the VSTest opt-in** — delete this from your project file:\n```xml\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nWith `MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0`, **Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the default**. The `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property was explicitly opting you *back* into the legacy runner. Simply removing it switches you to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\n**2. Run tests with the new CLI**\n\n```bash\n# Instead of:\ndotnet test\n\n# You can now also use:\ndotnet test          # still works (via MSBuild integration)\ndotnet run --project YourTest.csproj -- --list-tests   # direct MTP CLI\n```\n\n**3. Key behavioral differences to be aware of:**\n\n| Area | VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| `--filter` syntax | `dotnet test --filter \"Name~Foo\"` | Same syntax still works |\n| `.runsettings` | Fully supported | Supported, but some adapters may differ |\n| Console output | via `vstest.console` | New streamlined output |\n| Parallel control | `MaxCpuCount` in runsettings | `--maximum-failed-tests`, `--parallel` flags |\n\n**4. If you use a `.runsettings` file**, verify it still applies correctly — most settings carry over, but review any VSTest-specific nodes.\n\n**That's it** — since you're already on `MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0`, the SDK handles the platform wiring. The only required change is removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0961aa84-028d-4567-8482-ae223cc0b77f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty and there's no relevant project-specific documentation. Let me answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and the migration from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":466,"requestId":"D004:81B49:600EF11:6B487A2:69EC0F05"},"id":"e5e6b001-32be-4f58-80ff-ac1b7d69a6dd","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:47:14.054Z","parentId":"a9e97e94-3843-41a3-9bcc-80694bc2dbff"}
